item.title: ‘Crazy times’: New outbreak in Qld
item.description: Popular Brisbane cafe The Jam Pantry has closed and will carry out deep cleaning after a woman, who has since tested positive for COVID-19, dined there at the weekend.

item.title: Infections rise again in Victoria
item.description: Victoria has recorded 240 new coronavirus cases overnight, just 24 hours after a welcome drop in infections.

item.title: Virus link to youth worker: report
item.description: A youth detention centre worker has tested positive to COVID-19, according to reports.

item.title: Strong winds prompt bushfire caution
item.description: Firefighters have warned strong winds on Thursday could fuel an out-of-control bushfire burning in northern NSW just south of the Queensland border.

item.title: Cops net huge ice haul in Sydney raids
item.description: Three people have been arrested after police swooped on several properties across three Sydney suburbs on Wednesday, seizing $465,000 worth of ice and $78,000 in cash.

item.title: Qantas profits plunge 91 per cent
item.description: Qantas profits have plunged 91 per cent in what the premier airline has called “the most challenging period in its long history”.

item.title: Quarantine dodgers partied with rapper
item.description: Western Australia could soon have 100 extra Australian Defence Force personnel after two women breached hotel quarantine to party with an amateur rapper.

item.title: Icy blast to sweep NSW
item.description: NSW residents heading to the snow have been warned blizzards and avalanches threaten to sweep across the Snowy Mountains.

item.title: One found dead in fatal Toowoomba blaze
item.description: One person has been found dead after a house was destroyed by fire in a regional Queensland town on Wednesday night.

item.title: Cops allege spit attack on bus driver
item.description: Police allege a Melbourne bus driver has been spat on by a passenger.
